  "\u0000SKIP#146\u0000 will invoke its effect once after the initial render of the component and then again after every render in which a value in its dependency array has changed since the previous render.": "",
  "Here's a simple example that is updating our analytics whenever a user visits a new page.": "",
  "In almost every scenario, this is what you want. You're synchronizing your component with some outside system and as such, you want to re-synchronize whenever a dependency changes. In our case, we want to update our analytics whenever a user visits a new page.": "",
  "However, what do we do in a scenario like this?": "",
