  "That gets React off our back but it's obviously not ideal since now anytime \u0000SKIP#153\u0000 changes, our effect will re-run and mess up our analytics.": "",
  "This is (kind of) what React's \u0000SKIP#155\u0000 hook allows us to do. However, instead of using it to tell React which reactive but non-synchronizing values we want to use inside of \u0000SKIP#156\u0000, we can use it as a way to abstract those values into their own event handler which we can then use inside of \u0000SKIP#157\u0000 - without needing to include it in the dependency array.": "",
  "Similar to how event handlers allow us to abstract our side effect logic out of React's rendering flow, \u0000SKIP#159\u0000 allows us to abstract our reactive but non-synchronizing values out of \u0000SKIP#160\u0000.": "",
